    <body>
        
        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <seg type="supplemental">Ch<hi rend="superscript">s</hi>. Darwin Esq<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>.</seg>
                    <salute>Sir</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>Having laid before the Lords &amp;c your Letter of the 16 Inst inclosing the Account of Mess<hi rend="superscript">rs</hi> Smith &amp; Elder for the first part of the Work entitled The Zoology of the Voyage of H.M.S. Beagle, which is now published, amounting to the sum of £68.10.10. I am commanded by their Ldps to acquaint you that this pay<hi rend="superscript">t</hi>. will be made to Mess<hi rend="superscript">rs</hi>. Smith and Elder at any time by M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>. Sargent,<ref target="#foot.f1"/> at this Office, on their Application; and that payment will in like manner be ordered to be made hereafter on the receipt of a Certificate from you of the Sum required to be paid, accompanied by a document of the same nature as that now transmitted.— <lb resp="#mjhawkins"/> 23<hi rend="superscript">d</hi> Feb. 1838 <lb resp="#mjhawkins"/>A Y Spearman</p> 
                </div>
            </div>

        </div>
        
        
        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1"><ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_8072.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">William Sargent</ref>.</note>
        </div>
    
    </body>
